      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>ifloat<sup>®</sup> is an independent, innovative, unique marine leisure products affiliate marketing website.</p>
      <p>We offer a sophisticated and powerful approach to finding marine leisure and boating products from our own comprehensive database and aim to provide the single most valuable boating products resource on the internet.</p>
      <p>At ifloat<sup>®</sup> we offer an extreme depth of information on the products we list. The primary source for this information is from the manufacturers of the products we present and put as much of this as is reasonably possible at your fingertips. There is no need to look elsewhere for specific product information, which is time saving; all information in one place. It is this level of detail that allows us to provide you with tools to differentiate and filter products with unprecedented speed and power.</p>
      <p>Once you are ready to buy what you have found, we make it easy to find the best price from our partners - senior suppliers in the marine leisure market, with large inventories and a solid track record of delivering quality products and service.</p>
      <p>It couldn't be simpler - find, buy, float.</p>
      
      <h2>Our History / about the founders</h2>
      <p>The founders are both are qualified to advanced university level and have long-serving backgrounds in engineering and humanities. This allows a blend of 'numbers' and 'letters' with the focus being on the practical, simple and efficient ways of creating a boating resource.</p>
      <p>The family's history in boating goes back over 80 years, from a sea-scouts saling cutter to the ownership in the '1930s' of the now-historic classic Mahaki B-class schooner (sail number B8), built by Arthur Logan in 1895 in Auckland, New Zealand (and still sailing). First sailing was self-taught at age seven in a ten foot clinker dinghy with a simple gunter rig, leading to a self-build by one of the founders, at age 15, of a Moth. Later on windsurfing became the draw and then on to modest doses of cruising.</p>
