      <h2>Moving on / how ifloat<sup>®</sup> came about</h2>
      <p>ifloat<sup>®</sup>  was born from our experience into the sailing gear that we needed to buy for an ocean voyage. We found the amount and consistency of product information was highly variable and affected our confidence that they were making good choices of the products on offer. Market research confirmed we were not alone in our product selection experience. One UK cruising yacht owner interviewed confessed to spending between 15 to 20 hours per month on the internet trying to find products needed to support his sailing. As a result, a gap in the market gap was identified and we were determined to create a simple, straightforward and knowledgeable resource to present manufacturer information with leading retailers' product offers, and so give back wasted time that could be better spent out on the water; the result is ifloat<sup>®</sup>. The ocean voyage will come later.</p>
      
      <h2>What we've created / the ifloat<sup>®</sup> Web Application</h2>
      <p>The site is supported by an innovative technical design and all available manufacturer product data is put at the centre of the user experience. In addition to the powerful Find option, which acts on all the user data entered, there are over 300 property icon-driven filters that give full control to the user over every piece of product data they have in mind to find what they want. All measurements are seamlessly selectable in either Imperial or SI/Metric systems (both are displayed) and for clothing, all manufacturer sizes can be directly selected to show every item of that size instantly; no more size table lookups. Any product for sale can be found quickly and easily.</p>
      <p>All products can be selected (without limit) for side-by-side differentiation, bought immediately, or stored for future purchase. For increased buying confidence, large detail product images are used (many in high-resolution size) so you can 'visually touch' the products and then access the available technical documentation and other supporting materials. Once ready to buy, you are taken to the selected retailer site (the ifloat<sup>®</sup> site including the find box remains visible with seamless switching between sites) to pay and go.</p>
